description: Reviewed depth-to-water measurements for Champaign County observation wells.

columns.name: P_NUMBER
columns.meaning: Unique ISWS identifier for the observation well.

columns.name: TIMESTAMP
columns.meaning: Unique time and date of measurement.

columns.name: RECORD
columns.meaning: Internal record number unique to each datalogger.

columns.name: DTW_FT_RAW
columns.meaning: Raw depth to water measurement in feet below measuring point.

columns.name: Water_Temp_F_Raw
columns.meaning: Raw groundwater temperature measurement in Fahrenheit.

columns.name: Batt_Volts
columns.meaning: Battery voltage of external battery at time of measurement.

columns.name: RecError
columns.meaning: Error code associated with a measurement outside the normal range.

columns.name: STICKUP_FT
columns.meaning: Vertical distance from land surface to the measuring point in feet.

columns.name: TOC_ELEV_FT
columns.meaning: Elevation of top of casing or measurement point in feet.

columns.name: DateTimeReceived
columns.meaning: Date and time data was imported into the database.

columns.name: DTW_FT_Reviewed
columns.meaning: Updated depth to water measurement in feet below land surface.

columns.name: DTW_FT_Flag
columns.meaning: Flag if depth to water measurements have been manually updated.

columns.name: Water_Temp_F_Reviewed
columns.meaning: Reviewed groundwater temperature measurement in Fahrenheit.

columns.name: Water_Temp_F_Flag
columns.meaning: Flag if groundwater temperature measurements have been manually updated.

columns.name: DateTimeChanged
columns.meaning: Date and time depth-to-water values were changed.

columns.name: Finalized_Flag
columns.meaning: Flag to indicate if depth measurements are finalized.
